cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.IR. 

This paper deals with learning patient representations directly from clinical notes, which is a natural language processing (NLP) task. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses deep learning techniques such as stacked denoising autoencoder and paragraph vector model, which are commonly used in machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI) research, hence cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also evaluates the performance of the learned representations in supervised setups, which involves classification tasks, and hence cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are also possible sub-categories.
